```class Solution {
public:
    bool canVisitAllRooms(vector<vector<int>>& rooms) {
        int n = rooms.size();
        vector<bool> visited(n, false);
        visited[0] = true;

        for (int i = 1; i < n; i++) {
            for (int key : rooms[i]) {
                if (!visited[key]) {
                    visited[key] = true;
                    return true;
                }
            }
        }
        return false;
    }
};
```

efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(n)
space complexity: O(n)
energy implications: LOW

Explanation:

We use a boolean array `visited` to keep track of which rooms have been visited. We start by visiting room 0 and mark it as visited. Then, for each room i, we iterate over the keys (keys are the numbers of the rooms that room i can unlock) and mark each key as visited if it hasn't been visited yet. If we find a room that hasn't been visited, we return true, indicating that we can visit all rooms. Otherwise, we return false, indicating that we cannot visit all rooms.

